Supporters of the detained leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, Nnamdi Kanu, in large numbers clashed with members of security operatives at the Federal High Court in Abuja on Tuesday.  This is as our correspondent observed that the supporters kept on chanting, “Holy Holy Holy, Nnamdi Kanu is another saviour”. The PUNCH reports that Kanu is currently being arraigned at the Federal High Court over some amended charges levelled against him by the Federal Government. This is as the lead counsel for the IPOB leader, Ifeanyi Ejiofor, on Tuesday, unveiled Mike Ozekhome (SAN) as the leader of the defence team for Kanu, whose trial resumed today before Justice Binta Nyako of the Federal High Court in Abuja. Some journalists who arrived at the court to cover the proceedings were also barred from accessing the court premises.  Source •Chief Mike Ozekhome, SAN ABUJA - Constitutional lawyer and human rights activist, Chief Mike Ozekhome, SAN, has been drafted into the legal team of Mazi Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB).This is as the case comes up today, Tuesday at the Federal High Court, Abuja amid… In "Top Stories" By Teddy Nwanunobi Abuja (Sundiata Post) — Leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu, was, on Tuesday, granted bail on health reasons in an Abuja Federal High Court 4 presided over by Justice Binta Nyako. Nyako, however, denied bail to three other pro-Biafra agitators, Chidiebere Onwudiwe, Benjamin Madubugwu… In "Top Stories" By Teddy Nwanunobi Abuja (Sundiata Post) — Leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu, on Monday, refused to go into the Federal High Court in Abuja for his case without being accompanied by some of his relatives and supporters. Earlier in the day, Biafran supports had gathered… In "Top Stories"